<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/855: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-24T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            24, 1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 2:55
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>14. Senate confirmed last night appointments of Melitón F. Porras and
                                Hernán Velarde as plenipotentiaries and Solon Polo as counsellor of
                                the delegation to the Washington meeting. Porras cannot arrive in
                                Washington before April 15th, Foreign Office therefore requests, as
                                stated in Embassy’s telegram 11, February 11,<note n="5" xml:id="d207fn5">Not printed.</note> that Department of State
                                arrange meeting on a date between 20th to 30th of April.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>